ou are on your path, and it is truly your path, doors will open for you where there were no doors for someone else.\n\n- Joseph\n|\nYou can be anything you want to be as long as you know who you are. Paradoxically, once you realize this, you begin to lose your sense of self.\n\n- Todd Crawshaw, Heretofore\n|\nIf you have a vision from God, It means you have the ability to fulfill it\n\n- Sunday\n|\nTo fill life with moments of happiness, be happy in the moment.\n\n- Debasish\n|\nWhat would come, would come...and you would have to meet it, when it did.\n\n- J.K. Rowling, Harry Potter and the Goblet of Fire\n|\nThe mind is a wonderful servant, but a terrible master.\n\n- Robin\n|\nWhat are you doing extra? That's what counts. That's when you're working hard - when you're going above and over what's expected of you' (102). - Tony Gonzalez, 'The Giant Within\n\n- Denzel Washington, A Hand to Guide Me\n|\nIt took me fifteen years to discover that I had no talent for writing, but I couldn't give it up because by that time I was too famous.\n\n- Robert\n|\nboys, girls and music . . why do they need gin?\n\n- Frank\n|\nInstead of vacillating, we need to value, acknowledge and trust our intuition for what it is, a sense of truth.\n\n- Laurie Nadel, Dr. Laurie Nadel's Sixth Sense: Unlocking Your Ultimate Mind Power\n|\nIf you have answered God’s call and made the decision to fulfill your calling, then the devil will try to destroy you\n\n- Sunday\n|\nShe marched to the door and said, 'if I ever marry, Patrick O'Sullivan, I shall make sure that my mate for life is a decent woman, or even, maybe, a book.\n\n- Joanna Trollope, The Rector's Wife\n|\nFor books continue each other, in spite of our habit of judging them separately.\n\n- Virginia Woolf, A Room of One's Own and Three Guineas\n|\nThe unreality of the past weeks lifted like a fog, but its residue remained. All of the past is like that, but most especially the parts that are out of the ordinary.\n\n- Madeline Claire Fran